Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer these brand new freestanding warehouses for sale, located at 42-44 Apex Drive, Truganina. The properties are situated in Truganina’s premier industrial locale – The Crossing. This is an industrial 3 zoned estate, which boasts unrivalled proximity to the residential precinct of Truganina and Tarneit.
 
The current Western Road Upgrade Project will be completed in 2021. This will ensure that Palmers, Dohertys and Leakes Roads will improve efficiency of travel time for businesses operating in Melbourne’s West. Access to the city and freeway network via Leakes Road, and to the north via Palmers/Robinsons Road will be improved by this upgrade. Apex Drive will eventually provide a major thoroughfare/shortcut for vehicles driving from Palmers to Forsyth Road, increasing exposure to passing traffic for this site. 
 
Wide roads, generous landscaping and zoning restriction will ensure that this is a clean and desirable estate for decades to come. The Commercial 2 precincts on Leakes Road provide two important neighbouring offices, retail, food outlets and other retail amenity. 
 
Each property features:
+ Total Building area 2,510sqm*
+ Two levels of corporate office and amenities of 260sqm*
+ High clearance canopy over loading areas
+ Two roller doors and two crossovers
+ Total site area of 3,660sqm*
+ 38 car spaces

Building features include:
+ Massive cubic capacity – 10m* high concrete panels
+ Clear span warehouse 
+ Four container height motorised RSDs – 5.5m H x 5m W
+ Motorised front sliding gate
+ Three phase power
+ Corporate office over two levels 
+ Heating/cooling
+ Modern façade and landscaping
+ Racking plans available on request


*approx.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, in conjunction with Cushman & Wakefield, are pleased to offer for lease, Centreland Park Industrial Estate located at 175 Palmers Road, Truganina, VIC.

The estate is situated on Palmers Road between Leakes Road and Dohertys Road. The Melbourne CBD is 18km* from the site, Melbourne Airport 20 kilometres* and Melbourne Sea Port 14 kilometres*. Access to the Western Freeway and Western Ring Road is approximately 4km north of the site via a Diamond Interchange on Palmers Road.  

Future controlled intersections will be provided on Palmers Rd and on Leakes Rd to allow dual access to the estate off Shiny Drive or Prosperity Drive.

The estate has a total area of 24 hectares* comprising building areas from 2,000sqm* through to 70,000sqm*.  
The flexible industrial zoning allows for a variety of warehouse and manufacturing uses.

Building features will include:
+ Air-conditioned office and amenities
+ High clearance warehousing
+ B-double truck access
+ Multiple on-grade roller shutter doors
+ Recessed loading docks
+ ESFR sprinkler system
+ Dedicated car parking spaces
+ Main road sites offer significant frontage and exposure

CBRE is pleased to offer 60 Saintly Drive, Truganina, for sale or lease.

Melbourne’s Western region has become a thriving industrial hub over the last decade, boasting countless national distribution centres. Occupiers are drawn to the area based on its proximity to the Port of Melbourne, the extensive freeway network, competitive leasing rates and booming residential population. Surrounded by built out industrial estates, the Axiom Estate on Robinsons Road has been closely monitored by those looking to secure a premium location. 

The estate boasts a signalised intersection at its entry, this enables straightforward connectivity to the freeway network located less than 1km* away.

60 Saintly Drive, Truganina sits proudly at the entrance to the Axiom Industrial Estate.

After the completion of the Western Roads Upgrade Project, Robinsons Road will form part of a 21km north-south route linking the Calder Freeway in the north, down to Sayers Road, Williams Landing. Robinsons Road will be four lanes with plans for future expansion again. This road intersects with Ballarat Road, the Western Freeway, Boundary Rd, Dohertys Rd, Leakes Rd and other major east-west linkages.
